<br>
The sarnak are an iksar creation.  They are part dragon.  They were once slaves of the iksar, but no more.  The sarnak seek to destroy the dragons, the goblins, and the iksar and to dominate Kunark, as the Iksar do.  The ring of scale meddles in the affairs of all the races and outposts on Kunark, sending spies and creatures that can change shape.  The dragons pit the races against each other, causing deceit and suspicion and war.  <br>
<br>
You will note, that Venril Sathir, the great iksar necromancer, is pitted against the ring of scale.  One of the first things he did in his new rise to power is send the agent Korocust (spelled that wrong, probably!) to Chardok.  Korocust, armed with knowledge of his master, assasinated the Ring of Scale's agent to the Sarnak.  There are reports, however, that suggest Korocust may be a double agent, really working for the ring himself.  There is only one way to find out at this time.  Kill him, and dig through his belongings.<br>
<br>
The ring of scale broke off from the velious dragons, a long time ago, when it was declared by Yelinak that dragon would never fight dragon.  Trakanon was once a blue dragon, but is a poison dragon now after making a pact with bertoxxolus (yeah i probably spelled that wrong too).  Zlandicar is a cannabalistic dragon, living off of the remains of his fellow dragons in the necropolis.  Jaled Dar's shade sits in the necropolis, watching in horror as Zlandicar feasts on his remains.  He wants you to wake the sleeper so that the world will be destroyed..he wants both revenge and to be released.<br>
<br>
The two dragon factions do contact each other however.  Evidence suggests that the ring of scale has an emmisarry in the western wastes.  What happens next remains to be seen.<br>
